<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="support-vt">support <strong><em>vt</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /sə'pɔːt/    美 /sə'pɔːrt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>支撑；承受：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Is this bridge strong enough to support heavy lorries? 
这座桥禁得住重型卡车吗?</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>支持：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>These measures are <strong>strongly supported</strong> by environmental groups.  
这些措施得到环保组织的大力支持。</p><footer>2013 陕西</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>support sb in (doing) sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>They supported us in the struggle for an increase in pay. 
他们支持我们争取加薪。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>为...提供资金；供养：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The research was financially supported by the government. 
这项研究得到了政府的资助。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I had to work to support my family. 
我必须工作来养家。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.★ <strong>为...提供证据；证实：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Research supports the view that adolescents spend a great deal of time with their peers. 
研究证实了这一观点，青少年大量的时间是与同龄人待在一起的。</p><footer>2012 上海</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>supporter /sə'pɔːtə(r)/ n   </p></div>